WEBVTT

00:30.064 --> 00:34.068
[sultry piano music]

00:34.103 --> 00:40.040
♪ Words that we used to say

00:40.523 --> 00:45.010
♪ Back when we were dreaming

00:45.045 --> 00:50.257
♪ Larger than life, soaring

00:50.291 --> 00:53.018
♪ We were gold

00:53.536 --> 00:57.229
♪ Glowing warm and bright

00:57.850 --> 01:04.409
♪ You wrapped me up
So tightly with promises ♪

01:04.443 --> 01:11.243
♪ You said I'm not just
A mother ♪

01:11.278 --> 01:16.455
♪ A sister, a daughter

01:16.490 --> 01:21.219
♪ That I am much more

01:21.253 --> 01:24.394
♪ It's all over

01:24.877 --> 01:29.089
♪ There's no explanation

01:29.261 --> 01:33.472
♪ But it should have been us

01:33.921 --> 01:37.235
♪ I should be the one

01:37.269 --> 01:42.205
♪ Who caught your attention

01:42.240 --> 01:46.175
♪ Had all your affections

01:46.209 --> 01:49.385
♪ I was perfect

01:49.419 --> 01:56.185
♪ Gave you, everything

01:57.255 --> 02:02.329
♪ I thought we

02:02.363 --> 02:05.987
♪ Could have had it all

02:06.402 --> 02:10.923
♪ I could have stood
And made you ♪

02:10.958 --> 02:14.444
♪ So proud to know me

02:15.618 --> 02:22.832
♪ But, I won't go quietly

02:23.902 --> 02:28.320
♪ I won't be just some mother

02:28.355 --> 02:32.911
♪ Or sister or daughter

02:32.945 --> 02:36.294
♪ Or nobody

02:36.328 --> 02:41.989
♪ To be kept

02:51.205 --> 02:55.278
["Things Look Good"
by Sleeping in the Aviary]

03:24.100 --> 03:27.897
[saw grinds]

03:30.520 --> 03:33.040
[sparks zap]

03:35.145 --> 03:37.078
Here you go.

03:44.431 --> 03:47.054
How 'bout that autumn air, huh?

03:50.471 --> 03:52.232
How 'bout that autumn air.

03:52.266 --> 03:54.061
[truck approaches]

04:02.103 --> 04:04.658
Wake up, will ya.
I don't need to see that.

04:05.175 --> 04:07.039
Like I don't know who you are.

04:07.074 --> 04:10.111
Every freakin' time with the ID.

04:23.470 --> 04:25.126
Hey.

04:26.127 --> 04:28.268
How's the day going?

04:30.373 --> 04:32.410
Not much of a talker, huh?

04:58.159 --> 05:00.610
[city ambiance]

05:00.645 --> 05:03.613
[police siren wails in distance]

05:46.104 --> 05:48.417
[click]

06:10.784 --> 06:13.787
[dog barking in distance]

06:27.801 --> 06:31.321
[motorcycle sputters by]

06:44.265 --> 06:45.784
[static]

06:51.514 --> 06:54.344
[fly buzzing]

06:57.520 --> 07:00.489
[intermittent police radio
chatter]

07:02.836 --> 07:04.734
Hey.
Go back to where you were.

07:04.769 --> 07:06.460
- What's going on?
- Go back over there.

07:06.495 --> 07:08.393
- Get back over there.
- Get back over there.

07:08.428 --> 07:09.601
- Hey.
- Hey!

07:09.636 --> 07:11.500
Get back over there!
Alright.

07:11.534 --> 07:13.571
OFFICER 1:
What did you not understand?

07:13.881 --> 07:16.470
Get back to the other
side of the street.

07:16.505 --> 07:18.645
OFFICER 2:
Hey! Back up!

07:19.473 --> 07:21.268
- Right here?
- Right there's good.

07:21.302 --> 07:22.890
Okay, right there.
Don't move.

07:22.925 --> 07:24.616
STEVE: You're not gonna find
my prints on it anyway.

07:24.651 --> 07:25.928
I always wear work gloves.

07:25.962 --> 07:28.206
So you sure you didn't see
or hear anything strange

07:28.240 --> 07:29.552
last night?

07:29.587 --> 07:31.174
No.

07:31.209 --> 07:32.348
[thud from upstairs]

07:32.382 --> 07:33.832
Guys, I don't care
what you do up there

07:33.867 --> 07:35.455
but take it easy, okay?

07:35.489 --> 07:38.630
So last night.
Anything out of the ordinary?

07:38.872 --> 07:40.598
Nothing.

07:41.357 --> 07:43.635
- Nothing at all?
- Nothing.

07:43.670 --> 07:45.775
Sergeant Winslow...

07:46.431 --> 07:48.502
- Under the bed.
- I have a permit for that.

07:48.537 --> 07:49.779
DETECTIVE PHILLIPS:
You have a gun in there?

07:49.814 --> 07:52.161
Yeah. It's unloaded.

07:52.748 --> 07:54.681
SERGEANT WINSLOW:
Open it up.

08:26.885 --> 08:29.198
Put it back where you found it.

08:32.408 --> 08:34.443
DETECTIVE BERNARD:
I want to see that permit.

08:34.962 --> 08:38.621
- Right now?
- No, we can get to that later.

08:38.897 --> 08:41.969
Last night.
What time did you go to bed?

08:42.522 --> 08:43.832
One. One-thirty.

08:43.868 --> 08:45.663
And you didn't see
anything at all?

08:45.697 --> 08:48.493
I was in my garage all night.
I didn't see anything.

08:48.838 --> 08:50.564
BERNARD:
Mind if we take a look?

08:50.599 --> 08:53.394
[garage door loudly creeks open]

09:03.335 --> 09:04.992
PHILLIPS: Well, supposing
something were to have happened

09:05.027 --> 09:06.856
in your back yard
before you went to sleep,

09:06.891 --> 09:09.238
do you think you
would have noticed?

09:10.998 --> 09:12.793
I don't know.

09:12.828 --> 09:17.522
I had a few drinks out here and
I get pretty fixated on my work.

09:17.557 --> 09:18.937
BERNARD: Is this your job?

09:18.972 --> 09:20.732
STEVE: Yeah. I make
a little extra money

09:20.767 --> 09:24.840
fixing and refurbishing motors,
generators, stuff like that.

09:25.426 --> 09:28.395
- BERNARD: Extra?
- STEVE: Yeah. I'm a vet.

09:28.429 --> 09:31.778
- Oh, right: the leg.
- The leg.

09:32.744 --> 09:34.021
You own the place?

09:34.056 --> 09:35.954
STEVE:
My parents left it to me.

09:35.989 --> 09:37.611
BARNARD:
It's a pretty sweet deal.

09:37.646 --> 09:40.338
Government check, no mortgage.

09:40.372 --> 09:42.616
Get to tinker in
the garage all day.

09:42.651 --> 09:44.411
Yeah, it's super sweet.
Super sweet.

09:44.445 --> 09:47.759
All it cost me was my parents
and my ability to run.

09:47.794 --> 09:51.970
So tell me, soldier boy,
why on God's green Earth

09:52.005 --> 09:54.697
would someone dump a body
in your back yard?

09:54.904 --> 09:58.459
I don't know, man, you tell me.
I don't tinker as a detective.

10:01.980 --> 10:03.913
So that's your story?

10:04.465 --> 10:06.571
Honestly, there's nothing else.

10:06.606 --> 10:10.851
Funny thing is, when people say
honestly they're usually lying.

10:11.576 --> 10:13.820
- I don't lie.
- BERNARD: Oh come on!

10:13.854 --> 10:15.649
I'm not any good
at remembering my lies

10:15.684 --> 10:16.995
so I just tell the truth.

10:17.030 --> 10:18.790
- BERNARD: You never lie?
- Never.

10:18.825 --> 10:20.550
- Ever?
- Never.

10:20.585 --> 10:22.863
So, what you're not telling us

10:22.898 --> 10:24.865
is we should be
paying attention to.

10:24.900 --> 10:26.833
Guess you've got me figured out.

10:31.734 --> 10:34.875
What is it about me that
makes you think I'm an idiot?

10:34.910 --> 10:39.535
Tell me, is it my ears, my nose?
My suit?

10:39.569 --> 10:41.433
It's got to be something, Steve,

10:41.468 --> 10:44.471
'cause you're treating me
like I'm an idiot.

10:45.714 --> 10:47.750
You're hurting my feelings.

10:49.096 --> 10:51.927
Now come on. Can we work
together on this thing?

10:51.961 --> 10:54.792
- What thing?
- WINSLOW: What thing!?

10:54.826 --> 10:57.518
Oh, I don't know. We got
a vet with a history

10:57.553 --> 11:00.660
of violent outbursts and
a dead girl in his back yard.

11:01.937 --> 11:05.526
Now, why do I think you
had something to do with it?

11:05.561 --> 11:07.805
You suffer from dark thoughts.

11:10.152 --> 11:12.706
You're right. I do.

11:12.741 --> 11:15.053
It's a character flaw,
I'll admit it.

11:16.572 --> 11:19.989
But it is a real problem
for you.

11:20.024 --> 11:22.889
- [chuckles]
- Oh, okay.

11:22.923 --> 11:24.753
Then you wanna tell me
why we found her car

11:24.787 --> 11:26.858
parked a block from your house?

11:26.893 --> 11:28.411
STEVE:
So you know who she is?

11:28.446 --> 11:30.517
And you don't? Come on!

11:30.551 --> 11:32.864
Let me tell you, right now
you need to start thinking about

11:32.899 --> 11:35.142
what else we're gonna find
in that car.

11:35.177 --> 11:37.110
Like finger prints for example.

11:37.144 --> 11:40.803
Or better yet, start thinking
about how sweet

11:40.838 --> 11:43.772
you're gonna look to the boys
on cell block B.

11:44.462 --> 11:46.913
Now, you can either
give it up to them

11:46.947 --> 11:49.122
or you can give it up to me.

11:50.744 --> 11:54.092
That's funny. You think
you can run a game on me?

11:54.575 --> 11:56.750
You're right. I am!

11:56.785 --> 11:59.546
You're a perceptive guy, Steve.

12:01.513 --> 12:03.653
It's probably an accident,
right?

12:05.483 --> 12:08.417
These things happen.
It's understandable.

12:09.245 --> 12:13.663
But all of a sudden,
somebody ends up dead.

12:14.526 --> 12:17.702
I let you guys go through
my place, top to bottom.

12:18.876 --> 12:20.947
Been nothing but cooperative.

12:21.257 --> 12:23.915
Do you think I would do that
if I had something to hide?

12:23.950 --> 12:25.779
BERNARD:
So you don't know her?

12:25.814 --> 12:29.024
- No, I don't know her.
- PHILLIPS: Awful pretty though.

12:29.921 --> 12:33.097
- Don't you think so, Sarge?
- WINSLOW: Definitely a looker.

12:33.131 --> 12:36.928
Hell, I'd fuck her.
And I don't even like women.

12:36.963 --> 12:39.897
BERNARD:
And Steve here don't lie, right?

12:39.931 --> 12:44.694
So be honest, Steve, would ya?
Ya know?

12:45.109 --> 12:49.734
I don't want to get as blue as
Phillips here, but, would ya?

12:50.183 --> 12:52.219
With a dead girl?

12:52.254 --> 12:55.567
I don't know,
maybe that's your kink.

12:56.637 --> 12:58.225
Do I need a lawyer?

12:58.260 --> 13:01.746
This isn't TV, Steve,
just a witness interview.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.921
No Miranda necessary.

13:03.955 --> 13:07.787
We can always get you later.
Read you your rights then.

13:08.132 --> 13:09.892
There's nothing to get me for.

13:09.927 --> 13:13.068
PHILLIPS:
Then there's no reason not
to answer our questions.

13:15.001 --> 13:17.693
You're asking me
do I think she's pretty?

13:19.074 --> 13:20.800
PHILLIPS: Do you?

13:24.838 --> 13:27.185
I can honestly say...

13:27.220 --> 13:30.844
she's the most beautiful girl
I've seen in my entire life.

13:35.573 --> 13:41.510
[slow eerie music]

13:58.113 --> 14:00.046
Drop me at the corner.

14:08.640 --> 14:10.090
Oh, here he is!

14:10.125 --> 14:11.851
I seen that cop
drop you off, killer.

14:11.885 --> 14:13.300
How you like killing
helpless women, huh?

14:13.335 --> 14:15.993
- [kissing noises]
- Hey, I'm on the news tonight.

14:16.027 --> 14:18.236
I actually got some
compliments about you.

14:18.271 --> 14:20.307
- Weirdo!
- Yeah.

14:22.344 --> 14:24.139
Freak.

14:24.173 --> 14:26.037
[door slams shut]

14:43.123 --> 14:47.714
[eerie music]

15:17.226 --> 15:19.332
[glass shatters]

15:45.185 --> 15:46.876
FEMALE REPORTER:
It's been a chaotic day here

15:46.911 --> 15:49.776
in this usually quiet
neighborhood of New Britain.

15:49.810 --> 15:53.400
I'm here on Gautama Street
where, earlier this morning,

15:53.435 --> 15:58.785
at this house right behind me,
a man made a grisly discovery:

15:58.819 --> 16:02.375
the body of a young woman,
reportedly stabbed to death,

16:02.409 --> 16:05.205
lying lifeless
in his own back yard.

16:05.240 --> 16:07.380
Police were dispatched to
the scene when homeowner,

16:07.414 --> 16:09.727
- Steven Warren called 911...
- STEVE: Oh, nice robe.

16:09.761 --> 16:11.694
...stating that a woman,
who he did not know

16:11.729 --> 16:13.075
and appeared
to be deceased,

16:13.110 --> 16:15.146
was found propped up
in his back yard.

16:15.181 --> 16:18.736
The victim, 27-year-old
Diane Fae of New Britain,

16:18.770 --> 16:21.083
a talented singer
known for her performances

16:21.118 --> 16:23.016
with the local
community theater,

16:23.051 --> 16:24.984
was pronounced
dead at the scene.

16:25.018 --> 16:27.193
News spread quickly
and alarmed residents

16:27.227 --> 16:30.230
gathered in the streets, trying to make sense of this tragedy.

16:30.265 --> 16:33.371
A murder, on this street? It makes me sick to my stomach.

16:33.406 --> 16:34.890
STEVE:
How many kids you got, lady.

16:34.924 --> 16:37.341
All I can say is that I'm not
surprised the police are here

16:37.375 --> 16:40.792
right now. I'm sure
something bad happened,

16:40.827 --> 16:44.348
and, umm, hopefully the police
will figure it out.

16:44.382 --> 16:46.488
REPORTER:
Mr. Warren, who made
this shocking discovery,

16:46.522 --> 16:48.317
declined to be interviewed.

16:48.352 --> 16:51.458
We're told his family has owned the property for several decades

16:51.493 --> 16:53.322
and that he currently
lives alone.

16:53.357 --> 16:55.048
Few details are known
at this time

16:55.083 --> 16:56.912
about the victim's
cause of death,

16:56.946 --> 16:59.397
other than initial reports that she had been stabbed--

16:59.432 --> 17:01.434
[TV clicks off]

17:49.309 --> 17:51.035
Stop!

17:56.523 --> 17:58.594
Ugh, shit.

18:02.460 --> 18:04.462
Diane Fae.

18:04.497 --> 18:06.464
Here's to you.

18:09.502 --> 18:11.366
Wish I knew you.

18:12.298 --> 18:16.854
[sad music]

18:35.459 --> 18:39.359
Thanks for that.
Been a long time comin'.

18:49.438 --> 18:51.889
[ghostly whisper]
Tell me you love me.

18:52.476 --> 18:54.409
You promised.

18:56.652 --> 18:58.861
[glass shattering thud
from the roof]

19:18.467 --> 19:20.538
[door creeks eerily]

19:20.573 --> 19:22.506
MAL: Hey Steve-o!

19:23.369 --> 19:26.199
- Is this the right address?
- He's coming, he's coming.

19:26.234 --> 19:29.029
Steve-o!

19:30.169 --> 19:31.584
Here he is.

19:32.550 --> 19:34.587
You lose your crutch, killer?

19:34.621 --> 19:36.934
You guys banging around
out here?

19:37.176 --> 19:38.901
Are we whaa?

19:39.247 --> 19:41.559
Making noise?
It's not you?

19:42.319 --> 19:44.113
Uhmmm...

19:44.148 --> 19:46.219
You tossing some shit
up on my roof?

19:46.254 --> 19:47.634
Were you tossing
shit on his roof?

19:47.669 --> 19:49.188
- No.
- Are you sure?

19:49.222 --> 19:50.672
- Mm-hm.
- No.

19:50.706 --> 19:52.605
But maybe you're
hearing things though.

19:52.639 --> 19:54.676
Maybe noises from above.

19:54.710 --> 19:58.300
It's probably God knocking.
Maybe he's comin' to collect.

19:58.680 --> 20:00.647
What do you think, Mal?

20:01.683 --> 20:04.375
About what?
About... Oh yeah!

20:04.410 --> 20:06.412
I dunno.
Well maybe, I mean,

20:06.446 --> 20:09.035
I don't think God likes
guys who kill woman.

20:09.069 --> 20:11.106
I dunno.
Maybe that's just me.

20:11.140 --> 20:12.659
LENNY: No, probably not!

20:13.073 --> 20:15.352
You guys are cute,
you're having some fun.

20:15.386 --> 20:17.216
Listen, I catch you
on my property again

20:17.250 --> 20:18.527
it's gonna be trouble, okay.

20:18.562 --> 20:22.048
You already got trouble, killer.
Look.

20:23.187 --> 20:26.259
That's right, I'm a killer.
But I don't kill women.

20:26.604 --> 20:29.676
- Oh. Tough ex-Marine, right.
- Right.

20:29.711 --> 20:32.127
- Army.
- Army. Shit.

20:33.301 --> 20:34.440
- Let's go boys.
- All right.

20:34.474 --> 20:36.200
- Sidewalk. Let's go.
- Alright.

20:36.235 --> 20:39.134
Sidewalk.
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

20:39.445 --> 20:41.032
Alright.

20:41.067 --> 20:42.620
Don't forget this.

20:43.380 --> 20:46.106
- My walkin' stick now, bitch.
- Yup.

20:48.281 --> 20:51.111
Looked like he was really about
to go at it with those two.

20:51.146 --> 20:54.356
Yeah. Then we'd
have to rush right over.

20:57.117 --> 20:59.085
[loud knock on car window]

21:00.017 --> 21:01.950
- BERNARD: Hard-dee-fuckin'-har.
- [back door opens and closes]

21:02.295 --> 21:04.021
Not funny, Chet.

21:04.055 --> 21:06.230
I thought it was.

21:07.749 --> 21:10.683
- Pack it up, kids.
- What? Why?

21:11.097 --> 21:13.582
We got Diane Fae's cell records.

21:13.617 --> 21:16.413
No calls to or from
a Mr. Steven Warren

21:16.447 --> 21:19.381
- to a Ms. Diane Fae.
- Are you kidding?

21:20.658 --> 21:22.419
Gets even better.

21:23.109 --> 21:27.044
No prints on the screwdriver...
or the car.

21:27.700 --> 21:31.290
Also, I got an expedited
toxicology report.

21:31.566 --> 21:34.293
She's doped to the gills.
Benzo.

21:35.363 --> 21:37.088
If she didn't die
from the stab wound,

21:37.123 --> 21:39.263
downers would have
killed her anyway.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.092
She have a prescription
for Valium?

21:41.127 --> 21:43.405
No, not according
to the husband.

21:43.440 --> 21:45.994
- It's worth looking into.
- WINSLOW: Maybe.

21:49.377 --> 21:53.726
If you guys wanna keep an eye on
him, it's your time, your dime.

21:53.760 --> 21:55.383
- Got it?
- Yeah, yeah.

21:55.417 --> 21:58.524
- Okay, Sarge.
- If not, get some sleep.

21:58.731 --> 22:01.078
- PHILLIPS: Goodnight, Sarge.
- Goodnight.

22:04.253 --> 22:10.639
BERNARD:
Did you know, a fae is
the same thing as a fairy?

22:12.538 --> 22:14.229
Fae...

22:14.263 --> 22:20.477
...a metaphysical, supernatural
or preternatural enchantress

22:20.511 --> 22:25.274
noted for their mischief
and malice.

22:29.486 --> 22:32.040
You are such a fucking dork.

22:33.282 --> 22:35.457
[car starts]

22:42.775 --> 22:46.226
[eerie piano music]

22:53.648 --> 22:55.719
I got your ass!

23:01.380 --> 23:02.622
Hey!

23:03.623 --> 23:05.073
I gotcha.

23:05.763 --> 23:07.282
Come here!

23:10.872 --> 23:12.460
Hi, Steve.

23:13.495 --> 23:15.394
That's my ride, Becca.

23:15.428 --> 23:17.465
That's the guy I've
been telling you about.

23:17.499 --> 23:19.432
You're early, handsome.

23:23.160 --> 23:25.404
DIANE: Why did you break
your promise to me?

23:25.645 --> 23:28.234
You said you'd be dead too.

23:40.211 --> 23:43.594
[wind rustling]

23:53.915 --> 23:56.193
I, uhh...

23:58.954 --> 24:01.509
I found another guy, Steve.

24:03.821 --> 24:05.685
Yeah, who's that, Skip?

24:13.210 --> 24:15.626
You can keep the Briggs
for parts.

24:15.661 --> 24:17.628
[scoffs]

24:27.569 --> 24:31.504
[commuters indistinctly
whispering]

24:36.682 --> 24:38.684
MAX: Saw you on the tube
last night, hot shot.

24:38.718 --> 24:41.203
How'd you end up with
a dead girl in the back yard?

24:41.238 --> 24:44.172
Somebody trying to
send you a message?

24:45.276 --> 24:48.210
You got a message for me?
I'm listening.

24:49.004 --> 24:51.248
Just a theory...

24:51.282 --> 24:53.630
[indistinct chatter]

24:55.701 --> 24:57.496
Oh.

24:58.704 --> 25:01.534
You're the guy. You're the
guy who found the dead girl.

25:01.983 --> 25:04.951
Mike, it's the guy from TV.
He found that dead singer.

25:05.849 --> 25:08.714
I heard that she was, like,
all bloody and disgusting.

25:09.024 --> 25:11.371
Actually, she was beautiful.

25:34.291 --> 25:36.604
Diane Fae.

25:37.846 --> 25:40.297
I know I know you.

25:41.609 --> 25:44.335
[police siren wails in distance]

25:51.377 --> 25:54.691
[police siren approaches]

26:28.828 --> 26:33.384
[engine rattles]

27:07.004 --> 27:09.489
[ghostly whisper]
Tell me you love me.

27:10.421 --> 27:12.492
You promised.

27:55.052 --> 27:58.746
[gun hammer cocking]

28:07.893 --> 28:09.791
[gun chamber slaps shut]

28:52.592 --> 28:56.079
[talking from outside]

28:56.113 --> 28:58.115
You motherfuckers!

29:07.815 --> 29:09.437
Hey!

29:10.024 --> 29:12.474
- Wassup?
- What is it with you guys?

29:12.509 --> 29:14.062
Thought we'd take a look
and see

29:14.097 --> 29:15.823
where you killed
that singer girl.

29:15.857 --> 29:18.515
Yeah, Lenny and I
were just talking...

29:18.549 --> 29:22.174
and, umm, we don't like guys who
kill women living on our street.

29:22.208 --> 29:24.141
- Okay.
- It's not good for the...

29:24.176 --> 29:26.523
- Ya know...
- Who wants the first punch?

29:26.557 --> 29:28.974
- What?
- First one's free.

29:29.008 --> 29:31.631
Okay, well... you serious?

29:31.839 --> 29:33.185
There's two of us
and one of you.

29:33.219 --> 29:34.911
You each get one.

29:34.945 --> 29:37.258
- We're gonna kill you.
- Sounds good, man.

29:37.292 --> 29:39.605
[laughing] Really?

29:39.916 --> 29:41.193
Wow.

29:43.126 --> 29:45.956
Alright, ya know, fuck it.
Let's just... Do it.

29:45.991 --> 29:47.544
- Lenny...
- Yeah.

29:47.578 --> 29:49.166
There ya go.

29:49.201 --> 29:50.858
Let me just...
I don't want to...

29:50.892 --> 29:52.549
Gotta save that for later.

29:52.583 --> 29:53.584
Do you want to?

29:53.619 --> 29:55.932
- All you, Mal.
- Really? That's nice of you.

29:55.966 --> 29:58.762
But, seriously, go.
I don't even wanna...

29:58.797 --> 30:00.799
Uh! Fuck!

30:02.145 --> 30:04.009
Get up, bitch, get up.

30:04.043 --> 30:05.907
Alright, Steve-O,
your fuckin' shot.

30:05.942 --> 30:08.807
Get up, my man, get up.
Oh fuck!

30:08.841 --> 30:10.601
[body thuds to the ground]

30:10.947 --> 30:13.121
Oh, that fuckin...

30:13.156 --> 30:17.091
Fuck. Ahh! Fuck, dude, my
fucking right and my left ear.

30:17.125 --> 30:18.230
Owww!

30:18.264 --> 30:20.163
I ever see you again,
I'm gonna fucking kill you.

30:20.197 --> 30:21.785
Yeah. I... I... Owww!!

30:21.820 --> 30:23.960
Owww! Alright! Fuck!

30:24.167 --> 30:25.685
STEVE: Take this fucking cane
with you!

30:25.720 --> 30:27.826
I don't want the fucking cane!

30:28.999 --> 30:32.623
[howling wind]

30:35.834 --> 30:39.009
[howling wind]

30:58.753 --> 31:00.962
Ya little prick.

31:13.733 --> 31:17.772
- [TV channel surfing zaps]
- Hey, babe! Can I get a beer?

31:18.186 --> 31:21.293
- What's the magic word?
- Abracadabra.

31:21.327 --> 31:23.847
Oh, you need to get a new joke!

31:24.089 --> 31:27.126
- [laughing]
- STEVE: Oh, someone's fast.

31:27.678 --> 31:30.923
- Oh, you're quick. Come here!
- No, no! Stop! Be careful!

31:30.958 --> 31:33.684
- Come here!
- [laughter]

31:33.892 --> 31:35.997
Stop tickling me!

31:36.273 --> 31:37.965
I'm gonna pee this couch!

31:37.999 --> 31:39.380
Oh, you're gonna
pee on the couch?

31:39.414 --> 31:41.623
-Yes.
-You're gonna pee. That's gross.

31:41.658 --> 31:43.349
[giggling]

31:44.040 --> 31:46.318
- Did you pee?
- No.

31:47.871 --> 31:49.838
Tell me you love me.

31:49.873 --> 31:51.599
I love you.

31:51.979 --> 31:55.361
[indistinct chatter from TV]

32:01.298 --> 32:02.886
DIANE: No, Steve.

32:03.128 --> 32:05.647
This is the only place
that we can be together.

32:07.235 --> 32:12.033
If you do what you promised, we
can be anywhere you want to be.

32:17.763 --> 32:19.351
Ah!

32:21.698 --> 32:23.700
Together forever.

32:24.804 --> 32:27.083
Together forever and ever.

32:34.193 --> 32:36.644
DIANE: Tell me you love me.

32:39.405 --> 32:41.407
MAX: Help you with something?

32:41.890 --> 32:43.375
Security camera.

32:43.409 --> 32:46.102
MAX: Yeah, I'd be paranoid
if I were you, too.

32:46.792 --> 32:48.690
You got it or not?

32:48.725 --> 32:50.692
MAX: So you been thinking
about my theory?

32:50.727 --> 32:52.901
Someone trying
to send me a message?

32:53.350 --> 32:55.974
No, I thought whoever
did it might come back.

32:56.871 --> 32:58.252
Hmm.

32:59.011 --> 33:00.944
Does this stuff even work?

33:01.289 --> 33:03.015
Yeah, it works great.

33:03.050 --> 33:05.086
Three-hundred-sixty-five days,
ten years,

33:05.121 --> 33:07.744
never failed me.
Then I went digital.

33:08.400 --> 33:09.849
How much?

33:09.884 --> 33:12.059
MAX: Everything all in,
for you, fifty bucks.

33:12.093 --> 33:14.993
- For me. Twenty.
- Twenty?

33:15.200 --> 33:17.029
Tapes. High grade,
premium tapes.

33:17.064 --> 33:18.997
I've worked on the camera.
I've worked on the deck.

33:19.031 --> 33:20.895
Everything in front of you
is gonna work fabulous.

33:20.929 --> 33:23.035
Work with me a little bit.
Forty-five dollars.

33:23.070 --> 33:24.933
Bunch of old stuff.
I'll give you twenty.

33:24.968 --> 33:26.970
Okay, the whole idea
of negotiation

33:27.005 --> 33:29.938
is meet somewhere in the middle.
Can you help me a little bit?

33:29.973 --> 33:32.734
- I got twenty.
- Twenty. Twenty cash?

33:32.769 --> 33:35.220
- Yeah.
- Fine. Done.

33:35.254 --> 33:37.049
I hope your killer
does come back.

33:37.084 --> 33:38.809
Me too.

33:48.819 --> 33:50.787
That's for glass.

33:51.098 --> 33:53.238
What's the point of that anyway?

33:53.272 --> 33:55.136
It's therapeutic.

33:55.481 --> 33:58.105
- Where's your cane?
- I threw it out.

33:58.415 --> 34:02.074
- Still got the limp, I see.
- Yeah. I'm working on it.

34:02.523 --> 34:05.250
How did that happen, anyway?

34:05.457 --> 34:08.011
Defending democracy.

34:08.253 --> 34:10.462
Benzodiazepine?

34:11.152 --> 34:12.878
Valium?

34:13.534 --> 34:16.433
Someone drugged her
and then they stabbed her?

34:16.467 --> 34:19.022
We, uh, we don't
know what happened.

34:19.436 --> 34:21.887
Maybe you know
something we don't.

34:22.922 --> 34:25.270
You're Bernard, right?

34:25.304 --> 34:28.376
- And you're Detective Phillips?
- That's right.

34:28.411 --> 34:30.929
Just trying to keep this
straight...

34:31.172 --> 34:33.380
'Cause Bernard's
the commie, right?

34:33.416 --> 34:35.003
[amused laughter]

34:35.038 --> 34:37.246
And you definitely
didn't know her?

34:37.282 --> 34:38.973
Again, no.

34:39.007 --> 34:41.009
Do you have any enemies?

34:41.871 --> 34:44.322
A few guys in the neighborhood,
a couple punks,

34:44.358 --> 34:46.152
giving me a hard time
about this.

34:46.187 --> 34:47.809
But no, I don't
have any enemies...

34:47.844 --> 34:49.259
not on this side
of the Atlantic.

34:49.293 --> 34:52.366
You took someone's
favorite seat on the bus...

34:52.849 --> 34:55.161
You complained that
your neighbor's rap music

34:55.196 --> 34:56.887
was too loud...

34:56.922 --> 34:59.338
You're banging somebody's
wife... Something like that?

34:59.373 --> 35:02.203
It's too weird to be
a coincidence for me too.

35:04.171 --> 35:06.207
I was thinking that
the killer always returns

35:06.242 --> 35:08.002
to the scene of the crime.

35:08.036 --> 35:11.212
So, I'm gonna get him on tape.

35:14.077 --> 35:15.561
And...

35:15.941 --> 35:19.910
you guys are amazing
and I hate to burst your bubble

35:19.945 --> 35:22.292
but you're not the first
with a theory

35:22.327 --> 35:25.261
that someone was trying
to send me a message.

35:25.295 --> 35:27.021
Or that I had an enemy.

35:27.055 --> 35:29.265
Guy that sold me
that had the same idea.

35:35.340 --> 35:38.066
Did you know
the victim was married?

35:39.309 --> 35:42.554
No.
I didn't see or read that.

35:42.588 --> 35:46.351
Husband thinks his little singer
was cheating on him.

35:47.593 --> 35:50.078
So now I'm bangin'
someone's wife?

35:51.563 --> 35:53.116
You guys want
some straight answers,

35:53.151 --> 35:55.118
give me some straight questions.

35:55.153 --> 35:58.190
- Were you fucking her, Steve?
- No.

35:58.466 --> 36:02.090
If I had been,
she'd still be alive.

36:02.125 --> 36:04.162
Ha! You would have
protected her, is that it?

36:04.196 --> 36:06.129
STEVE: That's right.

36:07.579 --> 36:13.240
One more question: Diane
performed on stage that night,

36:13.274 --> 36:18.141
she left the theater, and
no one ever saw her again.

36:18.176 --> 36:20.281
Is there a question?

36:20.316 --> 36:24.043
- Did you kill Diane Fae?
- No.

36:24.078 --> 36:26.598
Do you know
who killed Diane Fae?

36:27.150 --> 36:29.048
No.

36:29.083 --> 36:32.466
- Take a guess.
- Her husband maybe.

36:34.985 --> 36:36.435
Funny.

36:37.678 --> 36:40.301
He said the same
thing about you.

36:41.613 --> 36:44.995
Really strong opinion
on that particular point.

36:45.962 --> 36:48.275
Almost as strong as his alibi.

36:51.174 --> 36:53.452
BERNARD: And you're a local
celebrity now, Steve.

36:54.177 --> 36:57.422
Face is all over the news,
you're not a hard man to find.

36:58.285 --> 37:02.012
I think that you'd
better be watching your ass.

37:02.323 --> 37:04.429
Any other advice, commie?

37:05.568 --> 37:09.641
No.
But I have a fun fact for you.

37:10.020 --> 37:11.470
I'm dying to hear it.

37:11.505 --> 37:15.129
In our line of work,
there are no coincidences.

37:15.647 --> 37:18.719
You think the butler did it,
the butler did it.

37:18.753 --> 37:23.620
There's no mystery,
there's no TV whodunit.

37:24.207 --> 37:27.590
- It's always your best suspect.
- Not this time.

37:28.556 --> 37:31.179
The two of you will have
to do a little detective work.

37:31.214 --> 37:33.734
Or, perhaps we'll get lucky

37:33.768 --> 37:36.978
and the killer will return
to the scene of the crime.

37:37.738 --> 37:41.535
See, I think that you got
your little camera there

37:41.569 --> 37:45.228
to protect yourself from all
those enemies you don't got.

37:53.788 --> 37:55.687
I guess I scored
a hundred percent

37:55.721 --> 37:58.068
or I'd be taking another ride.

37:58.379 --> 38:00.347
Yeah.

38:01.209 --> 38:03.488
We know where to find you.

38:06.076 --> 38:08.976
[footsteps exit]

38:13.532 --> 38:15.603
[glass shattering]

39:08.553 --> 39:10.624
[door creaks open]

39:22.774 --> 39:26.156
[humming buzz
of TV turning on]

39:33.267 --> 39:36.719
[whirl of VCR
engaging videotape]

40:17.207 --> 40:20.210
[hum of TV and VCR]

40:32.637 --> 40:37.780
[slow, ethereal music]

41:19.994 --> 41:22.549
DIANE: I'm not giving you what
you want, Steve.

41:27.277 --> 41:30.453
- Tell me you love me.
- I love you.

41:34.975 --> 41:38.565
[echoing]
My body was flesh and blood.

41:39.462 --> 41:41.429
But there are
countless fragments

41:41.464 --> 41:43.708
that form my mind and soul.

41:44.985 --> 41:49.196
My hopes and dreams
were mine alone.

41:49.955 --> 41:52.751
I controlled my own destiny.

41:55.409 --> 42:00.345
And now, I'm just
an image to you.

42:01.519 --> 42:05.902
We'll never know what we
could have been, together,

42:05.937 --> 42:10.493
floating in this void
between time and space,

42:10.528 --> 42:15.636
all because you broke
your promise to me!

42:15.843 --> 42:18.432
I've already taken my medicine.

42:19.019 --> 42:21.469
Now do what you promised.

42:23.057 --> 42:26.544
[gagging off screen]

42:38.314 --> 42:40.972
[retching]

42:41.559 --> 42:43.595
Tell me you love me.

42:51.638 --> 42:53.916
[glass shattering thud
from the roof]

43:13.038 --> 43:15.662
[ghostly whisper]
Tell me you love me.

43:17.802 --> 43:19.907
I love you.

43:21.909 --> 43:24.809
You promised!
[scream]

43:25.603 --> 43:26.983
Whoa!

43:29.089 --> 43:30.918
No way.

43:35.682 --> 43:37.407
I love you!

43:40.100 --> 43:42.550
Diane, I love you!

43:45.692 --> 43:47.486
Come on!

43:48.522 --> 43:50.386
That is total bullshit.

43:54.770 --> 43:58.877
[plastic unwrapping]

44:07.714 --> 44:09.647
[glow stick hits floor]

44:28.424 --> 44:31.703
World of knowledge
at your fingertips. Come on...

44:33.118 --> 44:34.913
Ghost.

44:35.189 --> 44:37.536
Angry ghost.

44:38.123 --> 44:40.436
Very angry ghost.

44:42.438 --> 44:45.752
Okay.
Diane, here we go honey...

44:46.614 --> 44:48.409
"Ghosts or apparitions
of the dead..."

44:48.444 --> 44:51.827
[that's you, I guess]
"...or sounds associated

44:51.861 --> 44:55.762
with inexplicable disturbances
are the lingering

44:55.796 --> 44:59.144
emotional residue
of people who have passed."

45:02.182 --> 45:04.632
[clicks on and off flashlight]

45:07.221 --> 45:08.844
"They are unable to make
the transition from

45:08.878 --> 45:10.915
the physical state
into the spirit world,

45:10.949 --> 45:13.124
these lost souls..."

45:13.158 --> 45:15.609
...this is amazingly poetic.

45:15.782 --> 45:19.130
"These lost souls exist in a
limbic state of emotional shock

45:19.164 --> 45:23.721
induced by sudden death
or a lifetime of suffering...

45:29.899 --> 45:32.488
[indistinct mumbling]

45:32.971 --> 45:35.008
...unable to understand
what's happening to them

45:35.042 --> 45:37.113
until someone breaks through
to explain they must

45:37.148 --> 45:40.082
depart Earth's sphere to the
next state of consciousness."

45:41.152 --> 45:43.948
Awesome. Great.

45:43.982 --> 45:46.191
Diane, you're dead!

45:49.608 --> 45:51.645
Go into the light.

45:57.789 --> 45:59.929
All right, Diane,
here we go, then.

45:59.964 --> 46:01.759
Here's the goods, honey.

46:01.793 --> 46:05.176
"In nearly all chronologically
documented cases

46:05.210 --> 46:07.972
of escalating
supernatural phenomenon,

46:08.006 --> 46:12.770
leading to physical synergy,
witnesses report cold spots,"

46:12.804 --> 46:17.982
none of that, "sounds," check,
"voices," check,

46:18.016 --> 46:21.088
"shadows of figures...
[chuckling]

46:23.953 --> 46:26.611
...until the spirit or spirits
manifest their will

46:26.645 --> 46:28.958
to interact
with physical worlds,

46:28.993 --> 46:31.616
moving objects,
touching eyewitnesses,

46:31.650 --> 46:35.137
and in rare cases even being
known to harm the living."

46:43.007 --> 46:44.767
You know what...

46:52.292 --> 46:54.639
Bring it, Diane.

47:04.028 --> 47:06.720
DIANE: You promised!
[screaming]

47:15.280 --> 47:17.282
Are you Steven Warren?

47:17.317 --> 47:18.974
Yeah.

47:19.250 --> 47:22.840
I'm Markus Willeford,
Diane Fae's husband.

47:23.910 --> 47:26.533
Are you the one
who found my wife?

47:28.604 --> 47:31.607
I don't want any trouble.
I just...

47:33.264 --> 47:35.818
I just wanted to talk to you.
[voice breaking]

47:39.339 --> 47:41.513
I didn't have anybody else
to talk to.

47:41.548 --> 47:43.412
- What do you wanna talk about?
- I don't know...

47:43.446 --> 47:45.172
I just...

47:49.901 --> 47:51.765
Who would do this, Steve?

47:51.938 --> 47:54.319
Who would do this to my Diane?

47:54.354 --> 47:56.183
I don't know.

47:58.185 --> 48:00.118
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

48:00.843 --> 48:02.914
No. You needed this.

48:02.949 --> 48:04.709
I understand.

48:04.743 --> 48:06.884
I don't know what
I wanted to do.

48:07.919 --> 48:09.679
But I'm glad
it turned out like this.

48:09.714 --> 48:11.716
I'm glad that...
that we're just talking.

48:11.750 --> 48:13.304
STEVE: Me too.

48:15.962 --> 48:17.895
I failed her, Steve.

48:18.930 --> 48:22.313
And I was her number one fan.
I mean, that's how we met.

48:22.347 --> 48:25.109
Diane was amazing.

48:25.972 --> 48:28.215
She could sing
like an angel, and...

48:29.251 --> 48:31.149
I knew she was a handful

48:31.184 --> 48:32.944
but I felt like the luckiest
guy in the world

48:32.979 --> 48:36.154
when she called me up
and asked me to come get her.

48:38.087 --> 48:39.917
I thought I was saving her.

48:41.090 --> 48:42.781
But in the end, I just
turned out to be the one

48:42.816 --> 48:45.923
who was helping
destroy her dreams.

48:46.751 --> 48:49.029
All she wanted was to sing,
to be a star,

48:49.064 --> 48:50.928
and she should have been.

48:52.136 --> 48:54.172
It was my fault.

48:55.829 --> 48:59.833
Anything she did,
it was my fault!

49:00.454 --> 49:03.009
I mean, I tried. God,
I tried to give her a good life,

49:03.043 --> 49:05.218
some stability.

49:05.459 --> 49:07.806
But I could barely make ends
meet, let alone afford a place

49:07.841 --> 49:12.811
for her in New York,
and if I could have...

49:12.846 --> 49:15.366
none of this would've happened.
[crying]

49:15.953 --> 49:17.816
MARKUS: I'm sorry.

49:21.165 --> 49:28.172
Markus, I don't mean to be
disrespectful or weird

49:28.793 --> 49:32.693
but is there anything
strange happening to you?

49:32.970 --> 49:35.041
Where you live?

49:35.075 --> 49:36.801
MARKUS: What do you mean?

49:36.835 --> 49:40.356
STEVE:
All right, I'll just say it.
I think Diane is here.

49:41.323 --> 49:43.256
Like a ghost.

49:43.981 --> 49:45.741
Like a ghost?

49:45.775 --> 49:47.950
I've seen her right in
front of me, plain as day.

49:47.985 --> 49:49.434
Just like the two of us
talking, right here.

49:49.469 --> 49:51.850
- Okay!
- No! Please, please don't go!

49:51.885 --> 49:53.404
Please!

49:53.438 --> 49:56.269
I don't have anyone else
to talk to about this.

49:57.995 --> 49:59.962
Please sit down.

50:10.110 --> 50:15.150
Just hear me out and then if you
want to beat the hell out of me

50:15.184 --> 50:18.015
or whatever, I won't stop you.

50:20.293 --> 50:22.157
I was a soldier.

50:22.985 --> 50:25.022
In Afghanistan.

50:25.919 --> 50:27.990
Been awhile now.

50:28.508 --> 50:31.925
I saw a lot there.
I did a lot.

50:33.133 --> 50:36.343
And when they sent me home,

50:36.378 --> 50:39.139
I felt like I let
all my friends down.

50:39.898 --> 50:43.523
Like a lot of them
would have made it back

50:43.557 --> 50:47.044
if I'd have been there
to help them but...

50:50.875 --> 50:52.980
Death there is so ugly.

50:53.395 --> 50:55.500
It comes so quickly.

50:56.536 --> 51:00.160
And Diane, she was beautiful.

51:01.127 --> 51:03.094
She was perfect.

51:03.991 --> 51:06.063
And she was so sad.

51:06.477 --> 51:08.479
I felt like I could help her.

51:08.962 --> 51:10.826
Like I knew her.

51:12.966 --> 51:14.554
And then I knew the cops
would come

51:14.588 --> 51:16.521
and that they would
take her away

51:16.556 --> 51:20.249
and I didn't want to lose her
so I took a picture of her.

51:22.493 --> 51:24.909
And that's why
I think she's here still.

51:32.434 --> 51:34.401
You're an asshole.

51:35.885 --> 51:37.335
Seeing ghosts and...

51:37.370 --> 51:40.373
You, you need to see
a psychiatrist! God!

51:40.614 --> 51:43.030
You're lucky I don't...
Ohhh!

51:43.065 --> 51:46.103
- [footsteps exit]
- [door opens and slams shut]

51:48.933 --> 51:52.109
[tape whirring]

52:36.394 --> 52:40.191
[Markus crying]

52:51.098 --> 52:55.172
["Waiting Room Blues" by She Is
So Beautiful/She Is So Blonde]

53:34.728 --> 53:36.420
[aerosol can
bangs and ricochets]

54:34.340 --> 54:37.653
[high pitched hum of TV]

55:17.210 --> 55:20.627
[static from TV]

55:33.226 --> 55:36.333
[ghostly breathing]

